rating_comment: Nafisa apu's place is very comfortable and homely. Everything is well organized and Nafisa apu goes above and beyond to make you feel comfortable. Your privacy is ensured and you also get to have a very wholesome experience. Even though some people reviewed the place to be a bit backward, I found it to actually be well located. info: Rating, 5 stars,  · March 2023,  · Stayed one night
rating_comment:
I had a fantastic stay at Nafisa's Homestay! From the moment I arrived, Nafisa and her family made me feel incredibly welcome and comfortable. The room was clean, spacious, and had everything I needed, including a comfortable bed and a private bathroom.
Nafisa went above and beyond to make sure I had a great stay - she cooked delicious meals for me, showed me around the local area, and even helped me plan my itinerary for the rest of my trip. Her warmth and hospitality made me feel like I was part of the family.
The location of the homestay is little backward but still it's in a quiet residential area Plus, Nafisa's husband is happy to arrange transportation or provide recommendations for things to do in the area.
Overall, I highly recommend Nafisa's Homestay to anyone looking for a comfortable, welcoming, and authentic experience in Dhaka. Thank you, Nafisa and family, for an unforgettable stay!
